, passionate violence of terror, this book unpicks the contentious issues of regionalism, protest and violence. It offers an insight into a neglected area of France's past that continues to impinge on its future, infused with one of the most potent symbols of French culture: wine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aTerrorismzFrancey20th century. 0aWine and wine makingzFrancezLanguedocxHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aColonel Weber.  aComité Régional d'Action Viticole.  aFrench history.  aLanguedocian winegrowers.  aRégional protest movement.  aanti-Dreyfusards.  aanti-Jacobin uprising.  acooperatives.  aguerrilla style military tactics.  amilitant winegrowers.  amonarchism.  apolitical violence.  asocialism.  aterrorists.  aviti-cultural radicalism.1 aSmith, Andrew W.M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610111240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526101112423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526101112/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles